  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">North-East Girls Basic Education Initiative: Schools Meet the Learner Approach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Statistics (UNESCO/UIL Global Monitoring Report, 2015), have shown that Nigeria has 10.5 million children who are out of school, which is about the highest number in the world. Of the number of children who are out of school, nearly 6.3 million or 60 per cent, of them live in the northern part of the country. Of this figure, over 71% are girls and women. 

School Meet the Learner Approach (SMLA) is an innovative approach developed by UNESCO to be piloted in Bauchi State to increase access to education taking into account cultural, socioeconomic, religious and security situation in the northeast geo-political zone of Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
